Source: pg-dbms-metadata
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/HexaCluster/pg_dbms_metadata

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-dbms-metadata
Architecture: all
Provides: postgresql-pg-dbms-metadata
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Oracle DBMS_METADATA compatibility for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 pg_dbms_metadata provides SQL functions and procedures for extracting object
 DDL in a way compatible with Oracle's DBMS_METADATA package. It can retrieve
 DDL for tables, views, sequences, routines, indexes, constraints, triggers,
 types, dependent objects, and role grants.
